1 Mainland species-area curves are tri-phasic

When area is large enough, it will inevitably start to ovelap biome boundaries and continental boundaries, and the curve goes up.

1.1 Preston (1960) Ecology

1.2 Fridley (2005) Ecology

1.3 Storch et al. (2012) Nature

2 Can we use the SAR to estimate global (gamma) diversity?

  • We definitely cant use the Chao or rarefaction-based techniques.

  • The theory of the large-scale SAR is still underdeveloped.

  • Maybe, we can try to figure it out today!
